class:: TR808HatCh
summary:: TR-808 hi-hat resonator port from WaveDigitalFilters
categories:: UGens>Filters
related:: Guides/ChowDSPPorts

Description::

TR808HatCh follows the `HatResonator` block from the `TR_808` set in `WaveDigitalFilters`. The input is treated as an excitation for the hi-hat resonator circuit, which is implemented as a wave-digital network with the original oversampling shell and parameter mappings. In DSP terms this is a resonant, circuit-derived filter body rather than a full synthesized hat voice, so the final sound depends strongly on what excites it.

The TR-808 hi-hat family is known for bright metallic clusters with short noisy decays and a distinctly electronic edge. This block preserves the resonant coloration that gives those sounds their metallic bite, whether it is driven by impulses, pulse bursts, or other synthetic exciters.

The nonlinear diode update follows the wave-digital literature cited in the source tree, including "An Improved and Generalized Diode Clipper Model for Wave Digital Filters."

classmethods::

method::ar

argument::in
Input or excitation signal.

argument::freq
Resonant frequency in Hz. Clamped to `1000..20000`.

argument::res
Resonance amount, clamped to `0..1`. Internally mapped like the plugin via `1 - res`.

argument::mul
Output multiplier.

argument::add
Output offset.


